  <bioghist id="aspace_38eb8ed3bfd250624687d6ec5d99a067">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Lecturer and writer on matters of apportionment.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_4349dd44b31c906a3f8a507d86fe69c0">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, subject files, legal briefs and papers, and other material pertaining to Wells' career and interest in legislative representation and redistricting, including the Wells Vs. Rockefeller Supreme Court challenge, anti-gerrymandering legislation, presidential election system reform, and other legal cases concerning districting and reform.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_5abc1c5e64bbfe85e871466091b2990c">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>David I. Wells papers, #4917. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
