a0d" level="file"><did><unittitle>Presidential election system reform; the Electoral College</unittitle><container id="aspace_436b8a99a4e07c3cef52c704a04c132b" label="Mixed Materials [31924065463485]" type="box">12</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_a65c177a6cbebf69029aba82ed0ee514" level="file"><did><unittitle>Summaries of events &amp; cases, post- 1970 redistricting</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1970/1970">1970</unitdate><container id="aspace_2bd6f2c21b35efc9b7832d3799f4a897" label="Mixed Materials [31924065463485]" type="box">12</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_e5c2184da74ea748c1f65a0ea8bb0413" level="file"><did><unittitle>1992 N.Y.S. congressional redistricting, including D.W. plan submitted to task force</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1992/1992">1992</unitdate><container id="aspace_da5606de6c441473fdd3da69d3600e8a" label="Mixed Materials [31924065463485]" type="box">12</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_8d10b416844294fad5a4c95feea1c8d9" level="file"><did><unittitle>State-by-state files on redistricting, in alphabetical order, beginning with this box which runs from Alabama through Georgia</unittitle><container id="aspace_4eadeb4e07e888ebe23b66d177ed803b" label="Mixed Materials [31924065464202]" type="box">13</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_532ad94860a02419dd14a6670a45f0a5"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>State files contain various materials on redistricting in the state in general, as well as some correspondence and other material on D.W. involvements in the state. Note, for example, Colorado, where League of Women Voters successfully campaigned to get proposal drafted in part by D.W. onto the ballot through initiative process. Proposal passed (1974) and was incorporated into state constitution.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_8631649344a6ac8efdd51c12a8cba180" level="file"><did><unittitle>State-by-state files, continued (Hawaii through Missouri)</unittitle><container id=